        <num>CC 3469</num>
        <heading>3469.  Suspension of prescription</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3469.  Suspension of prescription
Prescription is suspended as between: the spouses during marriage, parents and children during minority, tutors and minors during tutorship, and curators and interdicts during interdiction, and caretakers and minors during minority.
A &quot;caretaker&quot; means a person legally obligated to provide or secure adequate care for a child, including a tutor, guardian, or legal custodian.</p>
        </content>
